  </section>

  <!-- Understanding Your Results -->
  <section class="section bg-stone-50">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <h2 class="section-title">Understanding Your Results</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <p>
          After you enter your information, the calculator shows three important numbers. Here's what each one means and why it matters for your business budget.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Monthly Payment</h3>
        <p>
          This is the amount you'll pay every month. It includes both principal (loan amount) and interest.
          Make sure this fits comfortably in your monthly cash flow. A good rule: monthly payment should not exceed 20% of your monthly revenue.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Total Interest Cost</h3>
        <p>
          This is the total interest you'll pay over the entire loan term. Lower interest rates and shorter loan terms reduce this amount.
          For example, a 36-month loan costs 30-40% less in total interest than a 60-month loan.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Total Amount Payable</h3>
        <p>
          This is your loan amount plus total interest. It's the complete cost of financing (not including down payment).
          Use this to calculate your total investment and compare against equipment ROI.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded">
          <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Important Note:</p>
          <p>
            Calculator results are estimates only. Your actual approval amount and interest rate depend on your credit profile,
            equipment age, and lender assessment. Contact <a href="/en/contact" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark underline">Ing Heng Credit</a> for accurate quotes based on your specific situation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Factors That Affect Monthly Payment -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <h2 class="section-title">What Affects Your Monthly Payment?</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <p>
          Four main factors determine your monthly payment amount. Understanding these helps you adjust your financing to fit your budget.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Equipment Price</h3>
        <p>
          Higher equipment price means higher monthly payment. For every RM 10,000 increase in price, expect monthly payment to increase by RM 200-350
          (depending on loan term and interest rate). Consider buying quality used equipment to reduce cost by 40-60%.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Down Payment Amount</h3>
        <p>
          Larger down payment reduces your loan amount and monthly payment. Paying 30% down instead of 10% can save you RM 150-300 per month.
          However, don't drain your working capital completely. Keep 3-6 months of operating expenses in reserve.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Interest Rate</h3>
        <p>
          Interest rate is based on your credit score, equipment age, and lender policy. In Malaysia, rates typically range from 7.5% to 12% per annum for equipment financing.
          Every 1% reduction in interest rate saves RM 50-150 per month on a RM 100,000 loan.
        </p>

        <h3>4. Loan Term Length</h3>
        <p>
          Longer loan terms spread payments over more months, reducing monthly cost but increasing total interest paid.
          Shorter terms mean higher monthly payment but less interest overall. Choose based on your cash flow and equipment lifespan.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Example Calculations -->
