      <h2 class="section-title text-center">5 Strategies to Reduce Monthly Payments</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Want to lower your monthly payment? Use these proven strategies to make equipment financing more affordable.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {reductionStrategies.slice(0, 3).map((strategy) => (
          <BenefitCard
            icon={strategy.icon}
            title={strategy.title}
            description={strategy.description}
          />
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        {reductionStrategies.slice(3).map((strategy) => (
          <BenefitCard
            icon={strategy.icon}
            title={strategy.title}
            description={strategy.description}
          />
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 prose prose-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <p>
          Test these strategies using our calculator. Change down payment, loan term, and interest rate to see immediate impact on monthly payment.
          Find the combination that works best for your business budget.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Calculator vs Actual Approval -->
  <section class="section bg-stone-50">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <h2 class="section-title">Calculator vs Actual Approval: What's Different?</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <p>
          The calculator gives you a starting estimate. Your actual approval may differ based on several factors.
          Here's what causes the difference and what to expect.
        </p>

        <h3>Factors That May Change Your Rate</h3>

        <h4>1. Credit Profile Review</h4>
        <p>
          The calculator uses a standard interest rate range (7.5-12% p.a.). Your actual rate depends on your credit score, payment history,
          and existing debt levels. Good credit history qualifies for lower rates. CCRIS issues or bankruptcy may increase rates by 1-3%.
        </p>

        <h4>2. Equipment Age and Condition</h4>
        <p>
          New equipment gets the best rates. Used equipment (5-10 years old) typically adds 1-3% to your interest rate.
          Very old equipment (10+ years) may require special approval or higher down payment. The calculator assumes standard equipment age.
        </p>

        <h4>3. Insurance Requirements</h4>
        <p>
          Most lenders require comprehensive equipment insurance. Insurance premium adds RM 100-500 per month to your total cost
          (depending on equipment value and coverage). The calculator does not include insurance costs in monthly payment.
        </p>

        <h4>4. Processing Fees and Charges</h4>
        <p>
          Some lenders charge processing fees (typically 1-2% of loan amount), stamp duty, or legal fees.
          These one-time costs are not included in the calculator but affect your initial investment.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 rounded">
          <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Get Accurate Quotes from Ing Heng Credit</p>
          <p>
            Use the calculator for budgeting and planning. When you're ready to apply, contact us for personalized quotes
            that reflect your actual credit profile and equipment details. We provide accurate payment amounts within 1 business day.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <CTAButton href="/en/contact" text="Request Accurate Quote" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Why Calculator Estimates Are Still Valuable</h3>
        <p>
          Even though actual approval may differ slightly, the calculator is valuable for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Initial budgeting and cash flow planning</li>
          <li>Comparing different equipment price points</li>
          <li>Understanding how down payment affects monthly cost</li>
          <li>Testing different loan term scenarios</li>
          <li>Deciding if financing fits your business budget</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <h2 class="section-title text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Common questions about using our equipment financing calculator and understanding your results.
      </p>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-4">
        {faqs.map((faq) => (
          <FAQItem question={faq.question} answer={faq.answer} />
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA Section -->
  <section class="section bg-primary text-white">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Calculate Your Monthly Payment?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Use our free equipment financing calculator now. Get instant payment estimates for excavators, lorries, forklifts, and more.
        No signup required.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center items-center">
        <CTAButton href="/en/calculator" text="Use Calculator Now" variant="secondary" size="large" />
        <CTAButton href="/en/contact" text="Talk to Financing Expert" variant="outline" size="large" />
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-primary-light">
        <p class="text-lg">
          <strong>Need personalized help?</strong> Our team provides accurate quotes based on your specific situation.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          WhatsApp: <a href="https://wa.me/60175700889" class="underline hover:text-accent">+60 17-570 0889</a>
